/ LeetCode: 3498
// Problem name: Reverse Degree of a String
// https://leetcode.com/problems/reverse-degree-of-a-string/
// Category: String, Math
// Approach:
// - Iterate through the string from left to right.
// - For each character, calculate its reverse alphabet position: 26 - (s.charAt(i) - 'a')
// - 'a' gives 26, 'b' gives 25, ..., 'z' gives 1.
// - Multiply reverse position with (i+1) [1-based index].
// - Keep adding to total sum and finally return the answer.

Solution
--
class Solution {
    public int reverseDegree(String s) {
        int total=0;
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            int value=26-(s.charAt(i)-'a');
            total+=(value*(i+1));
        }
        return total;
    }
}
--
